## Setup Instructions

### 1. Get OpenRouter API Key
```bash
# Visit: https://openrouter.ai/keys
# Create a new key
# Copy and paste below as OPENROUTER_API_KEY
```

### 2. Update Environment Variables
```bash
# Copy this template to backend/server/.env
cp backend/server/.env.template backend/server/.env

# Edit backend/server/.env with your credentials
nano backend/server/.env
```

### 3. Start Services
```bash
# Terminal 1: Start MongoDB (if running locally)
mongod --dbpath /path/to/data

# Terminal 2: Start ChromaDB (optional, for semantic search)
chroma run --path ./chroma_data

# Terminal 3: Start backend
cd backend/server
npm install
npm start

# Terminal 4: Start frontend
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

### 4. Verify Configuration
```bash
# Test LLM connectivity
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/chat \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query":"hello","sessionId":"test"}'

# Should return a response with LLM greeting
```

